         "id": "SECTION_mix",
         "text": [
            {
               "text": "### Repeated sums\n\nWhen studying the *Yupana Inka Tawa Pukllay* method for performing multiplications with the *Yupana*, we learned that one of the steps of this process consisted of writing a number as many times as we wanted to multiply it and, subsequently, reorganizing the numbers through a sum (<htcite0>; <htcite1>). Thus, we can understand multiplication in its essence as repeated sums of the same quantity (<htcite2>).\n\n#### And on the abacuses?\n\nSimilarly, we can also use the abacuses to perform consecutive sums of the same quantity until we reach the desired result. When performing these sums, we will need to alternate between consecutive sums in the same column, when the value does not exceed 9, and the use of complements, when the sum result exceeds 9.\n\n#### A practical case\n\nThe best way to understand this scenario is by performing, in practice, consecutive sums. We chose to demonstrate what happens in the successive sums of 4. In this scenario, we will always use the complement of 6 when the sum result exceeds 9, because **4 + 6 = 10**:",
               "source": [
                  {
                     "type": 1,
                     "uuid": "a62b520a-f443-4d83-ab51-b99c9a46dab8",
                     "text": "Dhavit Prem",
                     "page": "pp. 360 - 361",
                     "date_time": {
                        "type": "gregory",
                        "year": "2018",
                        "month": "-1",
                        "day": "-1"
                     }
                  },
                  {
                     "type": 1,
                     "uuid": "c4c2c00d-7878-42da-9cc4-060cd7f8d225",
                     "text": "History Tracers Team",
                     "page": "Yupana (multiplication)",
                     "date_time": {
                        "type": "gregory",
                        "year": "2024",
                        "month": "-1",
                        "day": "-1"
                     }
                  },
                  {
                     "type": 1,
                     "uuid": "eaa59295-fb80-4c33-b1e4-bcdf3c11dabf",
